
graycolormap(1)                Scilab Function                graycolormap(1)
NAME
  graycolormap - linear gray colormap

CALLING SEQUENCE
  cmap=graycolormap(n)

PARAMETERS

  n     : integer >= 1, the colormap size.

  cmap  : matrix with 3 columns [R,G,B].

DESCRIPTION
  graycolormap computes a colormap with n gray colors varying linearly from
  black to white.

EXAMPLE
  xset("colormap",graycolormap(32))
  plot3d1()

SEE ALSO
  colormap, hotcolormap, xset
